cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network congestion control experiment results with QUIC, proxy, and topology
  evaluation under varied latency and bandwidth constraints
abstract: This dataset captures network performance measurements from experiments
  evaluating congestion control algorithms, QUIC protocol behavior, and proxy performance
  under synthetic latency and bandwidth constraints. Three nodes (rapla, tapa, valga)
  executed client-server workloads with configurable scheduler settings, slow-path
  profiles, and traffic shaping rules. Large file transfers and energy metrics were
  logged alongside per-run network traces. Archive contents include environment setup
  scripts, topology configuration files, and structured result logs organized by experimental
  parameters.
